1
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:19,937
After Shih Lung took Taiwan in 1683,

2
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:21,238
most Ching officials

3
00:01:21,481 --> 00:01:23,973
favored abandoning the island.

4
00:01:24,217 --> 00:01:26,549
Yet Shih was opposed to such an idea.

5
00:01:26,787 --> 00:01:29,381
He stressed the importance of Taiwan

6
00:01:29,656 --> 00:01:31,818
and insisted on keeping the island.

7
00:01:32,125 --> 00:01:34,560
Shih submitted to the Ching Emperor

8
00:01:34,861 --> 00:01:37,125
his Memorial to the Emperor
on the Taiwan Issue,

9
00:01:37,364 --> 00:01:40,095
analyzing the pros and cons
of keeping Taiwan.

10
00:02:03,991 --> 00:02:06,790
Shih was an ex-military under
Cheng Cheng-kung

11
00:02:07,027 --> 00:02:09,860
who had combat experience

12
00:02:10,097 --> 00:02:11,963
along the southeast coasts
of China and near Taiwan.

13
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:14,293
He knew Taiwan's geographic location

14
00:02:14,534 --> 00:02:16,195
was crucial and could shield

15
00:02:16,436 --> 00:02:18,871
the four coastal provinces
in southeastern China.

16
00:02:19,239 --> 00:02:21,901
The Ching government finally
accepted his recommendation

17
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:24,236
to incorporate Taiwan into its domain.

18
00:02:24,544 --> 00:02:26,979
Yet the Ching administration
took an attitude to Taiwan,

19
00:02:27,214 --> 00:02:27,874
this small island oversea,

20
00:02:28,115 --> 00:02:30,914
that was different from its rule
on the mainland.

21
00:02:32,052 --> 00:02:34,885
Afraid of losing control
if immigrants increase,

22
00:02:35,122 --> 00:02:37,921
the Ching administration
issued proclamations to place

23
00:02:38,425 --> 00:02:40,587
tight limits on immigrants.

24
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:43,057
Immigrants were not allowed
to take family to Taiwan.

25
00:02:43,330 --> 00:02:46,789
Taiwan's officials and armies
rotated every three years.

26
00:02:47,034 --> 00:02:48,798
Building of castles and walls
was prohibited.

27
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:55,668
Despite the prosperity
of the Ching Dynasty,

28
00:02:56,243 --> 00:02:57,870
the restrictions on immigrants

29
00:02:58,111 --> 00:03:00,045
reflected the government's
attitude towards Taiwan,

30
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:03,443
that was at the empire's frontier.

31
00:03:14,294 --> 00:03:17,286
Under such conservative rule

32
00:03:17,531 --> 00:03:18,657
of frontier Taiwan,

33
00:03:18,899 --> 00:03:20,628
people living along coastal areas

34
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:22,460
of Fuchien and Kuangtung

35
00:03:22,703 --> 00:03:24,671
crossed the perilous Black Water Ditch

36
00:03:24,905 --> 00:03:27,465
in search of better lives.

37
00:03:39,586 --> 00:03:40,747
During this period,

38
00:03:40,987 --> 00:03:43,183
English physicist Sir Isaac Newton

39
00:03:43,423 --> 00:03:43,981
had already discovered the

40
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:47,159
law of universal gravitation
and invented calculus.

41
00:03:47,494 --> 00:03:49,189
Western history

42
00:03:49,429 --> 00:03:51,591
would be rewritten along with

43
00:03:51,832 --> 00:03:53,766
the discoveries in the physical world.

44
00:04:00,273 --> 00:04:02,765
Shih Lang died in 1696.

45
00:04:03,009 --> 00:04:04,773
That winter,

46
00:04:05,011 --> 00:04:07,673
in Fuchou a big fire gutted
the ammunition warehouse.

47
00:04:07,914 --> 00:04:10,679
More than 500,000 kgs of
gunpowder went up in smoke.

48
00:04:15,689 --> 00:04:16,417
The Fuchien grand coordinator

49
00:04:16,656 --> 00:04:18,385
thus sent an adviser,

50
00:04:18,625 --> 00:04:20,719
Hangchou scholar Yu Yung-he,

51
00:04:20,961 --> 00:04:23,123
to mine sulfur in Taiwan.

52
00:04:30,704 --> 00:04:33,264
Before Cheng surrendered,

53
00:04:33,507 --> 00:04:35,373
Taiwan had never offered
tribute to the Ching Dynasty.

54
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:37,941
Neither did it have official
trade relations with China.

55
00:04:38,178 --> 00:04:39,873
But Yu found Taiwan

56
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:42,241
to be a residence of the gods.

57
00:04:45,418 --> 00:04:47,546
He recounted his travel
to Taiwan in his

58
00:04:47,788 --> 00:04:50,120
journal Pai Hai Chi You,

59
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:51,551
a rare firsthand account

60
00:04:51,792 --> 00:04:55,023
of the sights and sounds
of Taiwan during that time.

61
00:05:01,334 --> 00:05:03,063
In the first lunar month 1697,

62
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:06,637
Yu's fleet left Hsiamen.

63
00:05:11,812 --> 00:05:13,678
In the morning of the 24th
day of the second lunar month

64
00:05:13,914 --> 00:05:16,940
the blue seawater turned dark.

65
00:05:17,184 --> 00:05:21,417
The fleet arrived at Luerhmen
through Black Water Ditch.

66
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:31,363
Upon their arrival,

67
00:05:31,598 --> 00:05:40,234
the small island of Taiwan,

68
00:05:42,709 --> 00:05:49,911
Tainan Prefecture City, Chulo County,

69
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:57,056
Fengshan, Huwei Harbor,

70
00:05:57,290 --> 00:06:05,129
and the coastal areas inhabited
Pingpu aborigines.

71
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:10,602
Yu and his party

72
00:06:10,837 --> 00:06:13,431
on the 7th day of the 4th lunar month, 1697

73
00:06:13,673 --> 00:06:16,074
left Tainan Prefecture City,

74
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:20,244
headed north on cow-driven carts.

75
00:06:23,183 --> 00:06:25,174
I came to Taiwan to mine sulfur.

76
00:06:25,418 --> 00:06:27,045
I've stayed in the city for two months,

77
00:06:27,287 --> 00:06:29,278
buying textiles, oil, sugar,

78
00:06:29,522 --> 00:06:32,014
casting woks, blades, axes, hoes,

79
00:06:32,259 --> 00:06:33,988
making all sizes of wooden buckets,

80
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:36,924
and measuring devices.

81
00:06:37,163 --> 00:06:38,221
Things are finally ready.

82
00:06:38,465 --> 00:06:41,833
The cloths will be traded for
sulfur with the aborigines.

83
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:43,763
The oil and woks are
for processing sulfur.

84
00:06:44,004 --> 00:06:46,029
Sugar is for use as food and
for bathing by the artisans

85
00:06:46,273 --> 00:06:48,742
to cleanse sulfur toxicity.

86
00:07:00,153 --> 00:07:01,712
Yu first visited

87
00:07:01,955 --> 00:07:04,219
the four major communities
of the Siraya tribe

88
00:07:04,457 --> 00:07:07,222
in present-day Tainan City.

89
00:07:18,204 --> 00:07:20,696
He changed carts upon getting
to each tribal community.

90
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:22,534
The cart was drawn by a cow

91
00:07:22,776 --> 00:07:24,574
and driven by locals.

92
00:07:24,811 --> 00:07:27,473
Yu crossed Tachou River (Yanshui River)

93
00:07:28,381 --> 00:07:30,315
Passing through Hsinkang commune
(Hsinshih, Tainan),

94
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:32,177
Chialiuwan commune (Sanhua, Tainan),

95
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:33,817
and Matou commune (Matou, Tainan).

96
00:07:34,054 --> 00:07:36,148
Although locals lived in the areas,

97
00:07:36,389 --> 00:07:39,791
trees were luxuriant and houses were neat.

98
00:07:40,026 --> 00:07:41,790
The communes were not worse
than the villages in China.

99
00:07:42,028 --> 00:07:43,496
Who said that the aboriginal
tribes were backward?

100
00:07:43,730 --> 00:07:44,424
How can you believe everything

101
00:07:44,664 --> 00:07:46,564
that other people have said?

102
00:07:54,174 --> 00:07:55,767
After crossing Pachang River,

103
00:07:56,009 --> 00:07:58,444
Yu arrived at Chulo mountain commune,

104
00:07:58,678 --> 00:08:02,137
belonging to Hoanya tribe.

105
00:08:02,382 --> 00:08:05,977
Theirs was a different culture.

106
00:08:15,695 --> 00:08:16,992
After they had crossed the river,
it rained.

107
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:18,391
They walked hastily for 15 kilometers

108
00:08:18,631 --> 00:08:20,929
to reach Tawu commune to spend the night.

109
00:08:55,702 --> 00:08:57,568
Today, I saw

110
00:08:57,804 --> 00:08:59,932
more and more locals with tattoos.

111
00:09:00,173 --> 00:09:02,608
Their earlobes were as big as bowls.

112
00:09:02,842 --> 00:09:04,469
Their hair was bound.

113
00:09:04,711 --> 00:09:07,874
Some were bound into three splits
or two horns.

114
00:09:08,114 --> 00:09:11,015
Others made chicken feather decorations

115
00:09:11,251 --> 00:09:12,912
and placed them on their hair

116
00:09:13,153 --> 00:09:14,814
for beauty.

117
00:09:40,914 --> 00:09:42,848
On the 12th,
Yu's party passed Yashu commune

118
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:44,209
(Changhua) and reached Tatu commune
(Tatu, Changhua).

119
00:09:44,451 --> 00:09:46,647
The uneven rocky road

120
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:49,321
resulted in a bumpy ride
on the cow-driven cart.

121
00:09:49,556 --> 00:09:51,524
The trip was exhausting.

122
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:55,251
The weeds and wild trees

123
00:09:55,495 --> 00:09:58,931
along the way were shoulder-height.

124
00:09:59,165 --> 00:10:01,259
Compared to areas south of Changhua,

125
00:10:01,501 --> 00:10:03,367
this looked like another world.

126
00:10:03,736 --> 00:10:05,500
Yu's party passed through the

127
00:10:05,738 --> 00:10:07,706
Babuza tribe in Panhsien commune

128
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:09,602
of Changhua City.

129
00:10:09,843 --> 00:10:12,369
They entered Tatu and Shalu communes,

130
00:10:12,645 --> 00:10:13,271
and arrived at Niuma commune,

131
00:10:13,513 --> 00:10:17,177
present-day Chingshui area
in Taichung County.

132
00:10:17,417 --> 00:10:20,853
The Papora people lived
in the three communes.

133
00:10:42,408 --> 00:10:45,867
It was dark and rainy on the 14th.

134
00:10:46,112 --> 00:10:47,307
We couldn't proceed.

135
00:10:47,547 --> 00:10:48,878
The rain stopped in the afternoon.

136
00:10:49,115 --> 00:10:52,016
We heard roaring tides

137
00:10:57,757 --> 00:11:00,089
similar to those in Chientang River.

138
00:11:00,326 --> 00:11:01,851
The roaring continued even at night

139
00:11:02,095 --> 00:11:02,960
People in the commune said

140
00:11:03,196 --> 00:11:05,790
“The waves were signs of rain.”

141
00:11:06,199 --> 00:11:08,190
It rained on the 15th and 16th.

142
00:11:08,434 --> 00:11:09,833
Ahead of us, Tachia River

143
00:11:10,069 --> 00:11:13,903
rose and was rampaging.
We were afraid to cross it.

144
00:11:25,418 --> 00:11:28,547
Days of rain flooded Tachia River.

145
00:11:28,788 --> 00:11:31,655
Although in a hurry
to complete his mission,

146
00:11:31,891 --> 00:11:34,826
Yu was forced to remain in
Niuma commune for 10 days.

147
00:11:35,061 --> 00:11:37,291
As the weather improved slightly,

148
00:11:37,530 --> 00:11:40,329
we took a risk and crossed the river.

149
00:11:48,942 --> 00:11:50,876
It was slightly sunny on the 17th.

150
00:11:51,110 --> 00:11:52,908
My bed was facing the mountain.

151
00:11:53,146 --> 00:11:53,942
The hazy fog had blocked

152
00:11:54,180 --> 00:11:56,512
my view for five days.

153
00:11:56,749 --> 00:11:59,343
It was impossible to see the mountain.

154
00:11:59,519 --> 00:12:03,080
So seeing the sky brighten up
cheered me up.

155
00:12:03,323 --> 00:12:05,018
I realized that the mountain blocked

156
00:12:05,258 --> 00:12:06,953
the fierce barbarians from us.

157
00:12:07,193 --> 00:12:08,683
I wondered how it is like

158
00:12:08,928 --> 00:12:11,056
deeper behind the mountain.

159
00:12:20,907 --> 00:12:23,205
Yu's party hurried up north.

160
00:12:23,443 --> 00:12:24,706
They passed Taichung Tachia's

161
00:12:24,944 --> 00:12:27,174
Tachia and Shuangliao communes.

162
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:30,314
Reaching Miaoli, they stayed overnight
in Wanli commune.

163
00:12:30,617 --> 00:12:33,780
The Taokas people lived
in the three communes.

164
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:37,848
After crossing the river,

165
00:12:38,091 --> 00:12:40,753
there were uglier cart drivers.

166
00:12:40,994 --> 00:12:43,361
Their backs were tattooed
with spots like the leopard's.

167
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:44,620
Men and women

168
00:12:44,864 --> 00:12:46,662
kept very short hair

169
00:12:46,899 --> 00:12:48,025
that cover their foreheads,

170
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:49,861
just like mendicant Buddhist monks.

171
00:12:52,505 --> 00:12:53,802
On the 26th day of the 4th lunar month,

172
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:57,533
Yu arrived at Nankan commune
in Luchu, Taoyuan.

173
00:12:57,777 --> 00:13:01,111
He described Nankan as full
of thistles and wild grasses.

174
00:13:01,347 --> 00:13:02,906
It is a lair for wild beasts

175
00:13:03,149 --> 00:13:05,550
and unsuitable for human residence.

176
00:13:06,719 --> 00:13:08,312
Having passed Nankan commune,

177
00:13:08,554 --> 00:13:09,715
Yu's party again

178
00:13:09,956 --> 00:13:12,152
traveled along the coastline

179
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:14,859
and arrived at Pali commune,

180
00:13:15,094 --> 00:13:18,120
the territory of the Ketagalan people.

181
00:13:20,099 --> 00:13:21,931
Yu's party rode small boats to pass

182
00:13:22,168 --> 00:13:25,229
through the narrowest path
on Tamsui River

183
00:13:27,073 --> 00:13:29,041
called Kantoumen,

184
00:13:29,275 --> 00:13:31,334
which is present-day Kuantu in Taipei.

185
00:13:31,577 --> 00:13:33,341
Upon reaching Peitou,

186
00:14:16,155 --> 00:14:18,681
Yu started to mine sulfur.

187
00:14:18,925 --> 00:14:20,791
Yu's party had survived diseases
and storms

188
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:23,758
passed through 27 aboriginal tribes,

189
00:14:23,996 --> 00:14:26,363
and crossed 96 rivers.

190
00:14:26,599 --> 00:14:29,591
They traveled from
present-day Tainan to Tamsui.

191
00:14:29,836 --> 00:14:32,100
After about 20 days,

192
00:14:33,106 --> 00:14:36,633
Yu finally finished his mission
in the 10th lunar month 1697.

193
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:38,037
He left Tamsui

194
00:14:38,277 --> 00:14:39,870
and returned to Fuchou to

195
00:14:40,113 --> 00:14:43,048
finish his journal of the Taiwan travel:

196
00:14:48,821 --> 00:14:50,915
Pai Hai Chi You.
The greatest contribution of his journal

197
00:14:51,157 --> 00:14:53,057
are records of the late 17th century

198
00:14:53,292 --> 00:14:56,387
tribes and geographies
in Taiwan's west coast,

199
00:14:56,629 --> 00:14:59,826
and literary contributions
to the humanities and history.

200
00:15:00,433 --> 00:15:02,492
His journal described many scenes,

201
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:04,499
phenomena, and aborigine tribes,

202
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:07,138
all of which were recorded
for the first time.

203
00:15:07,607 --> 00:15:08,597
Many of his descriptions,
in particular those of

204
00:15:08,841 --> 00:15:11,674
the many Pingpu tribes
in the west coast of Taiwan,

205
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:14,380
are today inexistent.

206
00:15:15,615 --> 00:15:16,946
Thanks to Yu Yung-he

207
00:15:17,183 --> 00:15:19,117
the brave traveler,

208
00:15:19,352 --> 00:15:20,751
we can experience Taiwan

209
00:15:20,987 --> 00:15:22,455
from 300 years ago,
at a time when the Han people

210
00:15:22,688 --> 00:15:26,818
did not migrate in large numbers
to this island.

211
00:15:37,203 --> 00:15:43,108
Going to Taiwan from China,

212
00:15:43,342 --> 00:15:49,406
one feels extreme apprehension.

213
00:15:49,682 --> 00:15:54,347
Half of those who go to the
hinterlands could exist on,

214
00:15:54,587 --> 00:16:03,154
but none of those who go to
Taiwan are ever seen again.

215
00:16:03,396 --> 00:16:07,458
Half of those who go to the
hinterlands could exist on,

216
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:19,339
but none of those who go to
Taiwan are ever seen again.

217
00:16:36,329 --> 00:16:40,823
I am Peng Jui-jun from Lufeng
in Huichou, Kuangtung.

218
00:16:41,067 --> 00:16:42,865
Because the administration prohibited

219
00:16:43,102 --> 00:16:45,696
the Kuangtung people

220
00:16:45,938 --> 00:16:47,929
from bringing their family to Taiwan,

221
00:16:48,174 --> 00:16:50,438
I asked my relatives to smuggle

222
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:54,271
my nine family members to Taiwan.

223
00:16:58,551 --> 00:17:00,383
At that time,
Taiwan still had vast areas of land

224
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:02,088
that remained idle.

225
00:17:02,321 --> 00:17:05,882
To poor farmers living along
coastal areas in Fuchien and

226
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:09,755
Kuangtung, despite all kinds
of danger crossing the sea,

227
00:17:10,563 --> 00:17:11,724
Taiwan was their only chance

228
00:17:11,964 --> 00:17:14,763
to improve their lives.

229
00:17:16,569 --> 00:17:19,368
The Hakka immigrants came
mostly from Kuangtung.

230
00:17:19,605 --> 00:17:21,733
The trials and tribulations of
the early Hakka immigrants,

231
00:17:21,974 --> 00:17:24,705
the contents of the ballad Tu Tai Pei Ko,

232
00:17:24,944 --> 00:17:26,844
were written

233
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:29,047
by the early Hakka immigrants.

234
00:17:29,282 --> 00:17:30,181
To this day,

235
00:17:30,416 --> 00:17:33,408
the ballad remains popular in Taiwan.

236
00:17:34,587 --> 00:17:35,816
Waves after waves

237
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:38,888
of coastal residents in China

238
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:41,958
bribed officials or became stowaways

239
00:17:42,194 --> 00:17:45,220
in their attempt to come to Taiwan.

240
00:17:51,504 --> 00:17:54,303
At that time, the Ching
administration was focused on

241
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:56,941
preventing rebellion in Taiwan.

242
00:17:57,176 --> 00:17:59,645
Consequently, the exodus from
Fuchien and Kuangtung

243
00:17:59,879 --> 00:18:01,540
was not managed with much enthusiasm.

244
00:18:01,781 --> 00:18:04,148
The administration instead set
many restrictions.

245
00:18:04,617 --> 00:18:07,245
Yet the restrictions were unable to curb

246
00:18:07,486 --> 00:18:09,511
the people's desire to cross the sea.

247
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:13,824
Hence, illegal immigration
along the coastal areas

248
00:18:14,060 --> 00:18:15,550
became rampant.

249
00:18:15,795 --> 00:18:19,026
Although illegal immigrants
faced dangers at sea,

250
00:18:19,265 --> 00:18:21,063
the danger was nothing
compared with snakeheads.

251
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:22,597
The atrocities the snakeheads
inflicted on the illegal

252
00:18:22,835 --> 00:18:24,496
immigrants was the scariest.

253
00:18:26,238 --> 00:18:29,139
The snakeheads were like
now's human trafficking gangs

254
00:18:29,375 --> 00:18:30,706
Illegal immigrants often

255
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:33,139
fell victim to these snakeheads.

256
00:18:33,379 --> 00:18:34,938
If during the trip,

257
00:18:35,181 --> 00:18:37,115
immigrants had disputes over money

258
00:18:37,350 --> 00:18:39,148
with the boat owner,

259
00:18:39,385 --> 00:18:41,717
they would be thrown overboard.

260
00:18:48,327 --> 00:18:50,455
Other immigrants could only watch

261
00:18:50,696 --> 00:18:52,323
as those thrown overboard drowned

262
00:18:52,999 --> 00:18:54,023
and were eaten by fishes.

263
00:18:56,702 --> 00:18:58,966
Sometimes, the snakeheads

264
00:18:59,205 --> 00:19:00,798
would leave the illegal immigrants

265
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:02,439
on their own at the beach.

266
00:19:59,065 --> 00:20:01,363
A popular saying from that time was:
Six died,

267
00:20:02,134 --> 00:20:06,071
three were stuck, and only
one was able to return.

268
00:20:06,639 --> 00:20:09,870
It described the hardship of
Chinese immigrants to Taiwan.

269
00:20:10,109 --> 00:20:11,736
It also described how

270
00:20:11,977 --> 00:20:14,412
only less than one-third of the immigrants

271
00:20:14,647 --> 00:20:16,741
were able to survive in Taiwan

272
00:20:25,891 --> 00:20:27,882
while most died.

273
00:20:28,127 --> 00:20:30,095
Because survival was not easy,

274
00:20:30,329 --> 00:20:32,696
a few were forced to return to the mainland.

275
00:20:33,566 --> 00:20:35,728
Despite atrocities by the snakeheads

276
00:20:35,968 --> 00:20:38,801
and dangers of the Black Water Ditch,

277
00:20:39,038 --> 00:20:41,598
the Han immigrants were undaunted

278
00:20:41,841 --> 00:20:44,572
in their search for a better life.

279
00:20:44,810 --> 00:20:46,437
These waves of immigrants

280
00:20:46,679 --> 00:20:50,047
would proceed to change Taiwan's history.

281
00:21:15,641 --> 00:21:17,405
The early immigrants

282
00:21:17,643 --> 00:21:18,667
needed to apply for permits

283
00:21:18,911 --> 00:21:21,175
from the government

284
00:21:21,413 --> 00:21:24,508
in order to cultivate ownerless lands.

285
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,616
After gaining possession of the land,

286
00:21:26,852 --> 00:21:29,253
they must pay taxes regularly.

287
00:21:29,755 --> 00:21:32,884
This is a permit to cultivate land

288
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:35,184
issued by the district
government of greater Taipei

289
00:21:35,427 --> 00:21:37,225
in 1709 (the 48th year of the
reign of Emperor Kanghsi).

290
00:21:40,699 --> 00:21:42,929
Obtaining the land was only the first step.

291
00:21:43,235 --> 00:21:45,067
Developing water sources

292
00:21:45,304 --> 00:21:47,534
in a nomadic farming society

293
00:21:47,773 --> 00:21:49,673
was also essential.

294
00:21:50,042 --> 00:21:52,238
Thus, the right to develop land

295
00:21:52,478 --> 00:21:55,209
was as important as the
acquisition of water sources.

296
00:21:55,948 --> 00:21:58,417
In areas where water was scarce

297
00:21:58,651 --> 00:22:01,177
the Han Chinese cultivated land

298
00:22:01,420 --> 00:22:03,218
to manage water for irrigation.

299
00:22:03,556 --> 00:22:05,354
Most rivers in Taiwan

300
00:22:05,591 --> 00:22:07,081
were torrents

301
00:22:07,326 --> 00:22:09,124
with irregular water flow.

302
00:22:10,496 --> 00:22:12,521
To ensure a steady supply of water,

303
00:22:12,765 --> 00:22:15,097
people during those days competed
for water.

304
00:22:15,434 --> 00:22:16,526
The construction of irrigation systems

305
00:22:16,769 --> 00:22:18,828
consolidated participating villagers

306
00:22:19,071 --> 00:22:22,302
into a unit that shared the same fate.

307
00:22:22,975 --> 00:22:25,774
They became more united in
times of conflict of interest

308
00:22:26,011 --> 00:22:27,479
and fought against outsiders.

309
00:22:28,581 --> 00:22:32,074
With cultivation came conflicts.

310
00:22:32,318 --> 00:22:35,686
Conflicts occurred wherever
interests were involved.

311
00:22:38,691 --> 00:22:41,820
In 1709, land cultivator Shih Shih-pang

312
00:22:42,061 --> 00:22:45,122
set up the Papao irrigation system
in Changhua plain.

313
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:48,732
It drew water
from Choshui River in Pitsaitou,

314
00:22:48,968 --> 00:22:52,097
Erhshui to irrigate farms
in eight blockhouses.

315
00:22:52,705 --> 00:22:55,231
The system covered most villages,
townships,

316
00:22:55,474 --> 00:22:57,340
and cities in today's Changhua County.

317
00:22:57,643 --> 00:23:00,635
Over 12,000 hectares of land
benefited from this system,

318
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:03,542
during the time the largest
hydraulic engineering project.

319
00:23:07,753 --> 00:23:11,553
In 1760, Kuo Hsi-liu also set

320
00:23:11,924 --> 00:23:16,418
up a large irrigation system
from Hsintien and Green Lake,

321
00:23:16,662 --> 00:23:20,064
passing through Tapinglin,
Chingmei, and Kungkuan.

322
00:23:20,299 --> 00:23:23,894
It supplied water to eastern Taipei plain.

323
00:23:31,977 --> 00:23:32,910
After nomadic farming communities

324
00:23:33,145 --> 00:23:35,273
developed in Taiwan,

325
00:23:35,514 --> 00:23:37,004
prominent family gradually emerged

326
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:39,013
in the Han communities.

327
00:23:41,220 --> 00:23:43,587
Some gained prominence due to
military merits,

328
00:23:43,822 --> 00:23:45,449
such as Wang Te-lu of Chiayi.

329
00:23:46,091 --> 00:23:48,116
Others passed the imperial exam and became

330
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:51,489
a government official such as
Cheng Yung-hsi of Hsinchu.

331
00:23:51,730 --> 00:23:53,425
Cheng was the first chin-shih
from Taiwan in more than 100

332
00:23:53,666 --> 00:23:55,930
years after Taiwan's inclusion
in the Ching Empire.

333
00:23:56,168 --> 00:23:58,830
There was also the Lin family from Wufeng,

334
00:23:59,071 --> 00:24:00,800
playing an important role

335
00:24:00,873 --> 00:24:02,272
in Taiwan's development history.

336
00:24:05,978 --> 00:24:07,309
To protect their own interests,

337
00:24:07,546 --> 00:24:09,571
some prominent families

338
00:24:09,815 --> 00:24:12,944
recruited and paid tenant farmers

339
00:24:13,185 --> 00:24:15,119
to become their private armies

340
00:24:15,354 --> 00:24:18,085
and created the so-called village militia,

341
00:24:18,324 --> 00:24:20,816
that the Ching administration
both loved and hated.

342
00:24:22,628 --> 00:24:25,461
For instance, Lin Wen-cha of Wufeng

343
00:24:25,698 --> 00:24:27,632
led Taiwan-trained militia

344
00:24:27,866 --> 00:24:29,061
to the mainland to suppress

345
00:24:29,301 --> 00:24:31,099
the Taiping Rebellion.

346
00:24:31,337 --> 00:24:32,634
Lin also helped the administration

347
00:24:32,871 --> 00:24:35,033
suppress riots in Taiwan.

348
00:24:35,274 --> 00:24:37,299
At a time when nationalism has yet
to take shape,

349
00:24:37,543 --> 00:24:39,341
the local militia

350
00:24:39,578 --> 00:24:41,478
of the Han Chinese nomadic
farming community

351
00:24:41,714 --> 00:24:43,842
cemented civilians

352
00:24:44,083 --> 00:24:47,178
and fostered a sense
of identity among villages.

353
00:24:47,419 --> 00:24:49,251
As the influence
of these prominent families

354
00:24:49,488 --> 00:24:50,853
increased,

355
00:24:51,190 --> 00:24:54,216
it started to threaten the ruling class,

356
00:24:54,460 --> 00:24:57,623
which finally led to joint suppression

357
00:24:57,863 --> 00:25:00,127
by imperial officials and its enemies.

358
00:25:13,312 --> 00:25:15,178
In the early days of the Ching rule
in Taiwan,

359
00:25:15,414 --> 00:25:18,315
public authority was weak
and corruption abounded.

360
00:25:18,550 --> 00:25:20,678
Civilians often engaged in self-help

361
00:25:20,919 --> 00:25:22,853
to resist Ching suppression,

362
00:25:23,088 --> 00:25:26,114
resulting in frequent civil unrest.

363
00:25:27,860 --> 00:25:30,124
Immigrants of different
ancestral origins organizing

364
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:33,593
village fraternities for mutual assistance

365
00:25:33,832 --> 00:25:35,425
were also involved in frequent conflicts

366
00:25:35,667 --> 00:25:38,261
that resulted in armed violence.

367
00:25:38,504 --> 00:25:40,199
The society during that time

368
00:25:40,439 --> 00:25:42,601
was full of violence.

369
00:25:48,981 --> 00:25:50,676
Armed violence and civil unrest

370
00:25:50,916 --> 00:25:52,907
led to a major social confrontation

371
00:25:53,152 --> 00:25:56,247
once every five years

372
00:25:56,488 --> 00:25:57,819
until finally the largest

373
00:25:58,057 --> 00:26:01,027
revolt against the Ching rule erupted.

374
00:26:07,166 --> 00:26:20,944
Chaos under the Ching rule
caused civilians sufferings.

375
00:26:21,180 --> 00:26:32,785
Fighting factions caused much agony.

376
00:26:33,025 --> 00:26:45,404
Abuse was rampant during the
60th year of Kanghsi's reign.

377
00:26:45,971 --> 00:27:01,411
Chu revolted against the Ching
and became dominant.

378
00:27:05,557 --> 00:27:08,458
In 1721, the 60th year of the reign
of Emperor Kanghsi,

379
00:27:10,829 --> 00:27:13,958
Unable to stand paying heavy taxes
to Taiwan magistrate

380
00:27:14,199 --> 00:27:16,361
Wang Chen, duck farmer Chu Yi-kuei

381
00:27:16,602 --> 00:27:18,570
rose up in arms.

382
00:27:34,419 --> 00:27:36,285
Revolutionary forces followed his lead

383
00:27:36,522 --> 00:27:37,182
and swiftly captured

384
00:27:37,422 --> 00:27:41,188
Fengshan, Taiwan, and Chulo counties.

385
00:27:41,426 --> 00:27:43,121
As the resistance movement gained force,

386
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:11,319
Chu's forces finally captured
Tainan Prefecture City.

387
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:26,970
However,

388
00:28:27,206 --> 00:28:28,731
after Kuangtung Hakka leader Tu Chun-ying

389
00:28:28,974 --> 00:28:31,204
and his forces

390
00:28:31,443 --> 00:28:33,036
walked out on Chu,

391
00:28:33,278 --> 00:28:35,576
the largest rebellion against the Ching

392
00:28:35,814 --> 00:28:37,908
during its rule of Taiwan

393
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:39,879
was finally subdued.

394
00:28:56,368 --> 00:29:01,932
In fall of the 51st year of the rule
of Emperor Chienlung.

395
00:29:02,174 --> 00:29:09,604
Lin Shuang-wen's upheaval
caused anxiety to civilians.

396
00:29:09,848 --> 00:29:13,944
Lin captured Fengchu in Changhua County.

397
00:29:14,186 --> 00:29:15,847
18 townships and villages were affected

398
00:29:16,088 --> 00:29:19,524
In 1786, Lin Shuang-wen of
the Earth and Heaven Society

399
00:29:19,758 --> 00:29:22,455
formed alliances in Changhua
to rebel against the Ching Dynasty.

400
00:29:22,694 --> 00:29:24,788
The rebels had enormous following.

401
00:29:25,030 --> 00:29:26,225
Except Taiwan Prefecture city,

402
00:29:26,465 --> 00:29:29,526
other areas were captured.

403
00:29:29,768 --> 00:29:33,068
The Ching Empire sent troops
to suppress the rebellion,

404
00:29:33,305 --> 00:29:35,467
at one time reaching a high of 100,000.

405
00:29:35,707 --> 00:29:38,267
The rebellion, which lasted 16 months,

406
00:29:38,510 --> 00:29:39,272
finally ended

407
00:29:39,511 --> 00:29:42,446
when Lin was defeated and captured.

408
00:29:42,914 --> 00:29:44,541
Historically,

409
00:29:44,783 --> 00:29:46,512
armed violence in the early 18th century

410
00:29:46,752 --> 00:29:49,016
occurred mostly in southern Taiwan.

411
00:29:49,254 --> 00:29:50,346
During the mid-18th century

412
00:29:50,589 --> 00:29:53,081
as immigrants moved north to farm,

413
00:29:53,325 --> 00:29:56,317
the number of armed violence in the north
of Choshui River increased.

414
00:29:56,561 --> 00:29:58,086
In the early 19th century

415
00:29:58,330 --> 00:30:00,765
as areas in Taipei and Yilan developed,

416
00:30:00,999 --> 00:30:04,731
the scale and scope of armed
violence progressively grew.

417
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:24,446
Civil unrests turned
into confrontations between

418
00:30:24,690 --> 00:30:27,489
the Minnan, Kuangtung,
and Changchuan peoples.

419
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:31,892
Between 1684 and 1788,

420
00:30:32,130 --> 00:30:34,895
immigrants were not allowed
to bring family to Taiwan.

421
00:30:35,133 --> 00:30:38,103
This also caused an imbalance
in the demographics then.

422
00:30:39,271 --> 00:30:40,602
Therefore, nomads referred to

423
00:30:40,839 --> 00:30:43,809
as lo han ka began to appear.

424
00:30:45,744 --> 00:30:48,679
As cultivation expanded and

425
00:30:48,947 --> 00:30:50,540
more immigrants arrived,

426
00:30:50,982 --> 00:30:54,247
conflicts from land disputes worsened.

427
00:30:54,886 --> 00:30:57,082
Armed violence among settlers
of different ancestral origins

428
00:30:57,322 --> 00:30:59,086
gradually increased.

429
00:30:59,858 --> 00:31:03,158
“Gods fight while the layman suffers.”

430
00:31:03,428 --> 00:31:04,395
This kind of saying spoke eloquently about

431
00:31:04,629 --> 00:31:07,826
partisan armed violence in
Taiwan under the Ching rule.

432
00:31:08,066 --> 00:31:10,262
At that time, over 200 villages
in Changhua County

433
00:31:10,502 --> 00:31:13,836
were affected

434
00:31:14,072 --> 00:31:15,767
and several hundred people were killed.

435
00:31:16,007 --> 00:31:18,601
Armed conflicts of varying
scales occurred everywhere

436
00:31:18,844 --> 00:31:20,812
and lasted for years.

437
00:31:21,079 --> 00:31:22,672
As the battles affected the innocent,

438
00:31:22,914 --> 00:31:24,848
farms were left unattended.

439
00:31:25,083 --> 00:31:28,053
Partisan armed violence
was the main cause of

440
00:31:28,286 --> 00:31:31,620
instability
in Taiwan during the Ching rule.

441
00:31:32,424 --> 00:31:35,052
The pain and suffering caused
by partisan armed violence

442
00:31:35,293 --> 00:31:37,125
were vividly described

443
00:31:37,362 --> 00:31:40,024
in ballads of early Taiwan.

444
00:31:40,732 --> 00:31:56,206
Behold the white streamer
outside the Lungshan Temple.

445
00:31:56,448 --> 00:32:10,591
Chilly wind circles the incense jar.

446
00:32:15,767 --> 00:32:28,044
Are wives crying for husbands
or fathers for their sons?

447
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:45,927
Their cries touch the heaven,
that morns for their lost.

448
00:33:04,850 --> 00:33:07,683
As waves of Han immigrants arrived,

449
00:33:07,919 --> 00:33:09,751
misfortune befell

450
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:12,286
the aborigines living in the island.

451
00:33:21,166 --> 00:33:24,101
Han-Kavalan county prosecutor
Ko Pei-yuan

452
00:33:24,336 --> 00:33:25,428
often saw Pingpu aborigines

453
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:28,298
being abused in the government building.

454
00:33:28,773 --> 00:33:31,504
He wrote the poem Shu Fan Ko:

455
00:33:34,913 --> 00:33:46,086
“People think raw barbarians
are as fierce as the tiger.

456
00:33:46,324 --> 00:33:52,593
People mock cultured barbarians
as wretched as mud.

457
00:33:52,831 --> 00:33:54,356
In Taiwan,

458
00:33:54,599 --> 00:33:56,567
the lands of mountain aborigines

459
00:33:56,801 --> 00:33:58,599
were being seized by the Han.

460
00:33:58,837 --> 00:34:00,532
Due to language barriers,

461
00:34:00,772 --> 00:34:02,467
the aborigines could not
relate the incidents

462
00:34:02,707 --> 00:34:04,539
to the local officials.

463
00:34:04,776 --> 00:34:06,744
The officials also sided
with the Han Chinese,

464
00:34:06,978 --> 00:34:09,948
making it more difficult for
the aborigines to seek justice.

465
00:34:10,415 --> 00:34:13,214
When leasing farmlands
from the Pingpu people,

466
00:34:13,451 --> 00:34:15,078
the Han Chinese took advantage of

467
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:17,152
the illiterate aborigines

468
00:34:17,389 --> 00:34:19,858
to draft lease contracts in their favor.

469
00:34:32,270 --> 00:34:34,204
Instead of the lease period,
the Han Chinese would

470
00:34:34,439 --> 00:34:37,033
indicate that the land was sold to the Han,

471
00:34:37,275 --> 00:34:39,334
and let the aborigines sign the contracts.

472
00:34:39,811 --> 00:34:41,745
When the aborigines filed
complaints with the

473
00:34:41,980 --> 00:34:44,472
government during disputes,

474
00:34:44,716 --> 00:34:47,617
the Han Chinese connived with
interpreters to manipulate

475
00:34:47,852 --> 00:34:49,547
facts and cause the aborigines
to lose lawsuits

476
00:34:49,788 --> 00:34:51,381
and their lands

477
00:35:33,331 --> 00:35:34,730
The Han Chinese learned
that the Pingpu people

478
00:35:34,966 --> 00:35:37,731
were very scared of corpses
and dirty things

479
00:35:37,969 --> 00:35:39,095
so they deliberately left

480
00:35:39,337 --> 00:35:41,772
unclean things in the farm

481
00:35:42,007 --> 00:35:43,600
to scare the aborigines

482
00:35:43,842 --> 00:35:45,503
and make them leave.

483
00:35:52,917 --> 00:35:55,887
While they cultivated
and developed Taiwan,

484
00:35:56,121 --> 00:35:58,590
the Han immigrants used deception
and force

485
00:35:58,823 --> 00:36:00,348
to acquire vast areas of lands

486
00:36:00,592 --> 00:36:02,321
from the aborigines.

487
00:36:02,560 --> 00:36:05,495
This reduced
the aborigines' means of livelihood

488
00:36:05,730 --> 00:36:08,028
and threatened their survival.

489
00:36:17,776 --> 00:36:19,710
Before the Han Chinese came,

490
00:36:19,944 --> 00:36:21,105
the Pingpu aborigines

491
00:36:21,346 --> 00:36:24,839
led nomadic lives.

492
00:36:25,083 --> 00:36:26,482
During the Ching rule,

493
00:36:26,718 --> 00:36:28,186
the waves of Han Chinese immigrants

494
00:36:28,420 --> 00:36:30,388
brought immense cultural impacts

495
00:36:30,622 --> 00:36:32,590
on the aborigines.

496
00:36:32,957 --> 00:36:36,484
The Siraya tribe in the north
was the first to be affected.

497
00:36:37,195 --> 00:36:39,095
The Pingpu aborigines in the west

498
00:36:39,330 --> 00:36:40,456
continued to move until

499
00:36:40,699 --> 00:36:42,360
there was almost nowhere else to go.

500
00:36:43,935 --> 00:36:46,370
Most in the end had to adopt

501
00:36:46,604 --> 00:36:49,767
Chinese culture and use Chinese names,

502
00:36:50,008 --> 00:36:51,032
and the aborigines gradually

503
00:36:51,276 --> 00:36:53,574
lost their names and dialects

504
00:36:54,979 --> 00:36:55,537
Only a few, such as

505
00:36:55,780 --> 00:36:58,750
the Siraya and Kavalan,

506
00:36:58,983 --> 00:37:01,281
who had moved to remote places

507
00:37:01,519 --> 00:37:03,078
and avoided threats from the Han Chinese,

508
00:37:03,321 --> 00:37:05,949
were able to keep some of their culture,

509
00:37:06,191 --> 00:37:07,955
customs, and traditions.

510
00:37:29,948 --> 00:37:31,109
In the early Ching period,

511
00:37:31,349 --> 00:37:33,818
Han immigrants were forbidden
to bring family to Taiwan.

512
00:37:34,052 --> 00:37:34,985
Many single Han males

513
00:37:35,220 --> 00:37:38,019
married Pingpu women.

514
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:39,849
Doing so, they not only were able to marry,

515
00:37:40,091 --> 00:37:40,956
but also acquired

516
00:37:41,192 --> 00:37:43,991
rights to the lands of the aborigines.

517
00:37:44,596 --> 00:37:47,190
The Pingpu people lived
in a maternal society.

518
00:37:47,432 --> 00:37:49,196
They practiced matrilocal marriage

519
00:37:49,434 --> 00:37:51,528
similar to some of the Han Chinese.

520
00:37:58,209 --> 00:37:59,734
In a Siraya marriage,

521
00:37:59,978 --> 00:38:02,345
the couple refer to each other
as kan chi...

522
00:38:02,580 --> 00:38:05,242
No wedding ceremony was required.

523
00:38:05,483 --> 00:38:08,851
As long as the dowry was accepted,

524
00:38:09,587 --> 00:38:11,316
the marriage would be consummated.

525
00:38:12,157 --> 00:38:15,149
The groom could move into
the bride's home that evening.

526
00:38:16,694 --> 00:38:18,389
Today among Taiwanese,

527
00:38:18,963 --> 00:38:21,432
a husband refers to his wife as kan chiu,

528
00:38:21,666 --> 00:38:24,761
which originated from the
aborigine wedding tradition.

529
00:38:25,003 --> 00:38:27,438
This is also an instance
where the Pingpu dialect

530
00:38:27,672 --> 00:38:29,766
is assimilated into the Taiwanese dialect

531
00:38:31,743 --> 00:38:33,177
Through intermarriage,

532
00:38:33,411 --> 00:38:35,209
the Han Chinese

533
00:38:35,446 --> 00:38:37,005
bonded with the Pingpu people

534
00:38:37,248 --> 00:38:39,444
living in coastal areas.

535
00:38:39,717 --> 00:38:42,152
“A mainland husband
without a mainland wife”

536
00:38:42,587 --> 00:38:44,055
is a Taiwanese saying

537
00:38:44,289 --> 00:38:44,949
that best describes the

538
00:38:45,190 --> 00:38:48,751
bonding and assimilation of ethnic groups.

539
00:38:49,394 --> 00:38:50,589
The Pingpu culture

540
00:38:50,829 --> 00:38:53,628
has assimilated into the Han culture,

541
00:38:53,865 --> 00:38:57,301
and the Pingpu blood run through
many of today's Taiwanese.

542
00:39:06,878 --> 00:39:08,539
After the Lin Shuang-wen incident,

543
00:39:08,780 --> 00:39:09,440
to prevent reoccurrence of civil unrest

544
00:39:09,681 --> 00:39:11,843
many areas in Taiwan

545
00:39:12,083 --> 00:39:14,108
constructed city walls made of clay.

546
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:15,751
The emergence of city walls

547
00:39:15,987 --> 00:39:18,046
reflected the renewed mindset
of the Ching Dynasty

548
00:39:18,289 --> 00:39:20,257
in its rule of Taiwan.

549
00:39:20,491 --> 00:39:23,085
Taiwan was no longer an island
of barbarians.

550
00:39:23,361 --> 00:39:26,126
Taiwan also started to prosper

551
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:27,854
due to increased sea trades.

552
00:39:28,099 --> 00:39:30,227
After a long period,

553
00:39:30,468 --> 00:39:33,301
Taiwan had evolved from the
early-day immigrant society

554
00:39:33,538 --> 00:39:34,972
into a localized society

555
00:39:35,206 --> 00:39:37,732
with business potentials.

556
00:39:38,943 --> 00:39:40,377
A Taiwanese saying refers to three places:

557
00:39:40,612 --> 00:39:43,411
Tainan Prefecture City,
Lukang, and Bangka.

558
00:39:44,282 --> 00:39:46,751
These were the three major ports bustling

559
00:39:46,985 --> 00:39:49,044
with commercial activities.

560
00:39:49,287 --> 00:39:51,688
Since 1683,

561
00:39:51,923 --> 00:39:53,482
the busy ports have been testament
to the frequent

562
00:39:53,725 --> 00:39:56,194
and population movement across the Strait.

563
00:39:57,028 --> 00:39:59,963
The desolate world
Yu Yung-he saw during his time

564
00:40:00,198 --> 00:40:02,462
was now part of the past.

565
00:40:10,775 --> 00:40:14,336
After more than 100 years of Ching rule,

566
00:40:14,579 --> 00:40:17,947
the population in the plains
was how close to two million.

567
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:21,784
Aborigines living outside
the Ching-ruled areas

568
00:40:22,020 --> 00:40:23,920
also increased to over 100,000.

569
00:40:26,758 --> 00:40:29,386
They maintained their lifestyle,

570
00:40:29,627 --> 00:40:32,528
and lived in a closed,
self-sufficient society.

571
00:40:34,132 --> 00:40:37,124
This was just before
the European imperial powers

572
00:40:37,368 --> 00:40:40,065
began its invasion of the Ching Empire.

573
00:40:42,907 --> 00:40:45,808
Located in the southeastern
border of the Ching Empire,

574
00:40:46,044 --> 00:40:46,943
Taiwan's fate

575
00:40:47,178 --> 00:40:50,113
would again undergo a drastic change.

576
00:40:50,348 --> 00:40:53,443
In 1840, dispute between
the Ching Dynasty and Britain

577
00:40:53,685 --> 00:40:56,552
culminated in the Opium War.

578
00:40:56,921 --> 00:40:59,413
From 1841 to 1842,

579
00:40:59,590 --> 00:41:02,025
two British ships attacking

580
00:41:02,260 --> 00:41:05,252
Chilung Harbor and Taan Harbor in Taiwan

581
00:41:05,930 --> 00:41:08,126
were defeated by the stationed troops.

582
00:41:18,943 --> 00:41:21,469
More than 100 British soldiers
were captured.

583
00:41:21,713 --> 00:41:23,511
Apart from 30-odd soldiers
who died from illness,

584
00:41:23,748 --> 00:41:26,183
the remaining 139 Indian mercenaries

585
00:41:26,417 --> 00:41:28,852
were beheaded in public

586
00:41:29,087 --> 00:41:31,784
outside the city's north gate

587
00:41:32,023 --> 00:41:33,548
on the 13th of the 8th lunar month, 1842.

588
00:41:54,812 --> 00:41:56,746
Many years later,

589
00:41:56,981 --> 00:41:58,073
A Han Chinese witness

590
00:41:58,316 --> 00:42:00,080
recounted to a foreign reporter

591
00:42:00,318 --> 00:42:01,012
the horrendous mass killing

592
00:42:01,252 --> 00:42:03,914
during that time.

593
00:42:06,491 --> 00:42:07,322
Yes,

594
00:42:07,558 --> 00:42:07,990
I remember that day.

595
00:42:08,226 --> 00:42:10,194
It was a dark day for Taiwan.

596
00:42:11,529 --> 00:42:13,429
The execution started

597
00:42:13,664 --> 00:42:14,893
at about 9:00 a.m.

598
00:42:15,133 --> 00:42:17,363
and ended at noon.

599
00:42:17,602 --> 00:42:20,264
There were government officials
and thousands of onlookers.

600
00:42:20,505 --> 00:42:22,473
The sky had grown dark

601
00:42:22,707 --> 00:42:24,471
before the execution ended.

602
00:42:24,709 --> 00:42:26,006
There was thunder and lightning,

603
00:42:26,244 --> 00:42:29,179
and it rained for three successive days.

604
00:42:29,914 --> 00:42:30,779
Ah!

605
00:42:31,082 --> 00:42:33,107
It was the heaven condemning
the killing of foreigners.

606
00:42:33,584 --> 00:42:35,552
The brutal action
by the Taiwan government

607
00:42:35,787 --> 00:42:38,085
was to avenge the taking of

608
00:42:38,322 --> 00:42:40,620
Hsiamen by British fleet
during the Opium War.

609
00:42:42,293 --> 00:42:44,625
Although defeated

610
00:42:44,862 --> 00:42:47,422
in this battle at Taiwan,

611
00:42:47,698 --> 00:42:50,668
the British were victorious

612
00:42:50,902 --> 00:42:53,132
in major battles
along the coasts of China.

613
00:42:53,471 --> 00:42:54,336
The Ching Dynasty was forced

614
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:56,131
to sign the first unequal treaty

615
00:42:56,374 --> 00:42:58,536
in China's history.

616
00:42:58,776 --> 00:43:00,301
In the Treaty of Nanjing,

617
00:43:00,545 --> 00:43:02,980
Hong Kong was ceded to the British.

618
00:43:03,214 --> 00:43:04,340
In 1858, the British-French

619
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:07,483
Alliance forces once again defeated
the Ching army.

620
00:43:07,718 --> 00:43:09,277
The Ching Dynasty
signed the Treaty of Tienchin

621
00:43:09,520 --> 00:43:11,648
with the U.K., France,
and other countries.

622
00:43:11,956 --> 00:43:13,549
The treaty opened

623
00:43:13,791 --> 00:43:17,819
Taiwan's four major ports:

624
00:43:18,062 --> 00:43:20,929
Anping, Tamsui, Chilung,
and Takou to foreign trade.

625
00:43:26,537 --> 00:43:28,801
Closed for over 100 years,

626
00:43:29,040 --> 00:43:32,135
Taiwan's gate was open once again.

627
00:43:34,178 --> 00:43:37,011
Western and Japanese merchants,
adventurers,

628
00:43:37,248 --> 00:43:40,445
and missionaries came to Taiwan.

629
00:43:41,452 --> 00:43:44,717
The western world brought to
Taiwan a new civilization.

630
00:43:44,956 --> 00:43:47,982
Taiwan would meet the West

631
00:43:48,226 --> 00:43:50,126
and become connected to
the world scene once again.

